HEADWORD: Parochialism
<hw>Pa*ro"chi*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality
or state of being parochial in form or nature; a system of management
peculiar to parishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parochiality</ent>⟦br⟧
